  "summary": {
    "macroSummary": "Markets are experiencing a classic geopolitical risk-off to risk-on rotation as US-Iran peace talk hopes drive a broad relief rally across risk assets. Bitcoin breaking $74K and stocks rebounding while oil/dollar retreat suggests markets are pricing out immediate Middle East escalation risks, supporting the current oversold relief rally narrative.",
    "regimeImpact": "The peace talk optimism reinforces rather than changes the bear market relief rally assessment, as geopolitical de-escalation removes a key downside catalyst while underlying structural bearish factors remain intact.",
    "actionItems": [
      "Consider tightening BMNR cash-secured put strikes as Bitcoin breaks above $74K and approaches the $75K technical resistance level",
      "Monitor for potential short book covering opportunities if peace talks gain more concrete momentum and VIX continues falling from current levels",
      "Maintain Maturity sector overweight but watch for rotation signals if sustained risk-on sentiment emerges from successful diplomatic resolution"
    ],
    "keySignals": [
      "Bitcoin's $400M short squeeze above $74K indicates strong technical momentum that could challenge the $75K resistance and our $62,300 BMNR structural level thesis.",
      "10Y Treasury yields declining while stocks rally suggests the bond market is pricing out both geopolitical and inflation risks from the Middle East conflict.",
      "Dollar weakness concurrent with oil retreat creates favorable conditions for risk asset rallies and potential crypto outperformance.",
      "The Strait of Hormuz reopening focus and diplomatic progress represents the removal of a major binary risk that was weighing on the relief rally."
    ]
  },
